<GamepadEvent>
<summary>
The GamepadEvent interface of the Gamepad API contains references to gamepads connected to the system, which is what the gamepad events <see cref="Window.Gamepadconnected"/> and <see cref="Window.Gamepaddisconnected"/> are fired in response to.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para></para>
<para><see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Gamepad_API/Using_the_Gamepad_API">Using the Gamepad API</see></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/GamepadEvent"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
</GamepadEvent>
<GamepadEventGamepadEvent>
<summary>
The <strong><c>GamepadEvent()</c></strong> constructor creates a new <see cref="GamepadEvent"/> object.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/GamepadEvent/GamepadEvent"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
<returns>A new <see cref="GamepadEvent"/> object.</returns>
</GamepadEventGamepadEvent>
<GamepadEventGamepad>
<summary>
The <strong><c>GamepadEvent.gamepad</c></strong> property of the<br/><strong><see cref="GamepadEvent"/> interface</strong> returns a <see cref="Gamepad"/><br/>object, providing access to the associated gamepad data for fired<br/><see cref="Window.Gamepadconnected"/> and <see cref="Window.Gamepaddisconnected"/> events.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para><see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Gamepad_API/Using_the_Gamepad_API">Using the Gamepad API</see></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/GamepadEvent/gamepad"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
<value>A <see cref="Gamepad"/> object.</value>
</GamepadEventGamepad>
